<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-12-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-12-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="456" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d456">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Griscom</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-12-11"><hi rend="italic">December 11,
                                    1900</hi>.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Griscom requests that arrangements be made for the <hi rend="italic">Kentucky</hi> to remain a little longer in order that any
                            impression of hostility may be removed, and states that, with the
                            Department’s approval, he will go to Smyrna on December 13, if the
                            affairs of the legation will permit.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>